An Act removing the fee for veteran license plates.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 2 of chapter 90, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby
2 amended by inserting after the words “are veterans, as defined in clause Forty-third of section 7
3 of chapter 4” the following words:- , section 1 of chapter 115, or who is eligible for the annuity
4 provided under section 6C of said chapter 115
5 SECTION 2. Said section 2 of chapter 90, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
6 striking out, in lines 466 through 469, inclusive, the sentence: “There shall be an annual $20 fee
7 for such "VETERAN'' plates in addition to the established registration fee for private passenger
8 motor vehicles and motorcycles.” and inserting in place thereof the following sentence:- Any
9 such “VETERAN” plate shall be issued without fee other than the established registration fee for
10 private passenger motor vehicles and motorcycles.
